Each of these art glass cast cubes spent over 150 hrs in a computer controlled kiln being fused and refused. Between fusing they were cut and recut on a diamond wet saw. Then came as many as 8 steps of wet grinding and polishing each of their 6 sides.

Ways need to be found to put such a ridiculous amount of effort into such a modest outcome. The one used here was to embrace focus and repetition as a refuge. 

